Wake up every morning with Neal & Marga, start your day with a smile and get all the local information you need. 1 day ago in Lifestyle, Trending If you use Facebook, WhatsApp or Instagram, you\'ve probably noticed a new character pop up answering search queries or eagerly offering tidbits of information in your feeds, with varying degrees of accuracy. 2 days ago in Lifestyle Lab-grown meat is not currently available in any U.S. grocery stores or restaurants. If some lawmakers have their way, it never will be. 4 days ago in Lifestyle Experian suggests five ways to pay for a wedding while costs continue to increase. 4 days ago in Lifestyle, Trending A 35-year-old Brooklyn resident gave up buying new clothes. A 22-year old in San Diego swore off retail therapy at Target. A 26-year old in England banned carbonated drinks from her shopping list. 1 week ago in Lifestyle, Trending Travelers contended with big crowds and flight delays Friday, which was expected to be the busiest day of the Memorial Day weekend. 1 week ago in Lifestyle Even as millions of older adults clamor for drugs such as Ozempic and Wegovy, monthly use of the medications soared in people aged 12 to 25. That\'s according to the new analysis of dispensing records from nearly 94% of U.S. retail pharmacies from 2020 to 2023. 1 week ago in Lifestyle Cars, trucks and SUVs in the U.S. keep getting older, hitting a record average age of 12.6 years in 2024 as people hang on to their vehicles largely because new ones cost so much. 1 week ago in Lifestyle, Trending Daily and near-daily marijuana use is now more common than similar levels of drinking in the U.S., according to an analysis of national survey data over four decades. 14 hours ago in Sports The wet weather just keeps coming this week at the French Open. It has been delaying and postponing matches — including on Friday — jumbling the schedule, prompting court changes and, all in all, creating stress and uncertainty for the world\'s best tennis players. 14 hours ago in Sports After days of barreling along the huge waves of Tahiti\'s island paradise, French Polynesian surfer Vahine Fierro has even more reason to look forward to this summer\'s Olympics. 14 hours ago in Sports The Florida Panthers are on the verge of going back to the Stanley Cup Final for the second straight year and third time in franchise history because they are finding ways to win the tight ones. 1 day ago in Sports The Indiana State University and Boston Celtics great addressed a public ceremony Thursday for the official opening of the Larry Bird Museum inside the Terre Haute Convention Center. After the ceremony, Bird took questions from the media, which he jokingly said might be his last interview. 2 days ago in Sports Criminal charges against Scottie Scheffler have been dismissed, ending a legal saga that began with images of the world\'s top golfer being arrested and handcuffed in Louisville during the PGA Championship. 2 days ago in Sports Kendall Coyne Schofield once showed off her speed racing against men in a skills competition at NHL All-Star weekend. On Wednesday night, she sprinted into women\'s hockey history. 2 days ago in Sports Josh Gibson became Major League Baseball\'s career leader with a .372 batting average, surpassing Ty Cobb\'s .367, when Negro Leagues records for more than 2,300 players were incorporated Tuesday after a three-year research project. 3 days ago in Sports Catch up on the French Open with a guide that tells you everything you need to know about what happened at the clay-court Grand Slam tennis tournament, how to watch it, what the betting odds are, what the schedule is and more. 4 hours ago in National Marian Shields Robinson, the mother of Michelle Obama who moved with the first family to the White House when son-in-law Barack Obama was elected president, has died. She was 86. 14 hours ago in National Vermont has become the first state to enact a law requiring fossil fuel companies to pay a share of the damage caused by climate change after the state suffered catastrophic summer flooding and damage from other extreme weather. 1 day ago in National, Trending Donald Trump became the first former president to be convicted of felony crimes Thursday as a New York jury found him guilty of falsifying business records in a scheme to illegally influence the 2016 election through hush money payments to a porn actor who said the two had sex. 2 days ago in National Power outages scattered across storm-weary Texas on Wednesday could linger into the weekend after storms flooded streets in Houston for the second time this month and ripped off roofs in Dallas, leaving a teenager dead and injuring others. 2 days ago in National The jury in Donald Trump\'s hush money trial ended its first day of deliberations without a verdict Wednesday but asked to rehear testimony from key witnesses about the alleged hush money scheme at the heart of the history-making case. 14 hours ago in Entertainment Thirty years later, Nicole\'s three sisters want her remembered for more than those static images or the violent way she died. They fear the vibrant person they knew has been lost in the chaos of Simpson\'s murder trial, the questions it raised about race in America and the headlines spawned by his recent death. 14 hours ago in Entertainment The four members of the Swedish pop quartet ABBA, who triumphed at the 1974 Eurovision Song Contest with the peppy love song "Waterloo," on Friday got one of the most prestigious knighthoods in Sweden from the Swedish King Carl XVI Gustaf. 2 days ago in Entertainment Manhattan prosecutors told a judge Wednesday they are evaluating more claims of sexual misconduct made against Harvey Weinstein and could potentially seek a new indictment against him before his scheduled retrial on rape and sexual assault charges. 2 days ago in Entertainment Usher will add another prestigious award to his already loaded trophy case. The American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers said Thursday that Usher will receive its Voice of the Culture Award. 2 days ago in Entertainment Rapper and singer Sean Kingston on Tuesday waived his right to fight extradition in a California court and agreed to be turned over to authorities in Florida, where he and his mother are charged with committing more than a million dollars worth of fraud. 2 days ago in Local The state Attorney General says he did not reach this decision lightly. 3 days ago in Local The victim believed her grandson was in trouble and needed cash. 1 week ago in Local Triple A says more than 38 million are driving. 1 week ago in Local “We can never fully thank you for all the sacrifices you’ve made," Biden said to the veterans and their families. 2 weeks ago in Local The agreement means the Granite State and Quebec will combine efforts to protect shared borderland. 'version': '2025-01-09-base', 'language': 'en', 'pageNumber': 0, 'inputText': "Arielle joined the WMUR-TV team in October 2022 as a reporter. Before returning home to New England, Arielle worked as a reporter-producer at ABC News in New York, NY, where she helped manage the network's coverage of COVID-19 crisis. She covered a number of other major stories during her time at ABC, including the 2020 Presidential primaries and general election, the trial of former Minneapolis Police Officer Derek Chauvin, and the Surfside building collapse. She also helped conduct an extensive investigation for Diane Sawyer's 20/20 Special, 'Escape From a House of Horror,' which revealed the failures of officials in Riverside County, California, in their care for the 13 Turpin siblings, who had been placed under their protection, following their rescue from an abusive home. Arielle began her career at WMUR's sister station, WCVB-TV in Boston, where she worked first as an intern, and then as an Assignment Editor. A native of Cambridge, Massachusetts, Arielle graduated from Wellesley College in 2019 with a degree in Political Science and Women and Gender Studies. After walking onto Wellesley's Varsity Field Hockey team as a freshman, Arielle spent four years as an NCAA student-athlete. She helped her team to an NCAA Elite 8 appearance, and as a senior, she was elected captain of the squad. An avid runner, Arielle has completed five Boston Marathons. She also enjoys swimming, cheering on the Boston sports teams, and spending time with her friends and family. Arielle is thrilled to join the incredible team at WMUR-TV, and to be back home in New England. Hearst Television participates in various affiliate marketing programs, which means we may get paid commissions on editorially chosen products purchased through our links to retailer sites."}]

Two democratic incumbent state representatives lost their party’s nominations after redistricting earlier this year shuffled things around. In Cheshire District 7, which covers Keene’s Ward 2, Rep. John Bordenet lost to Shaun Filiault, and in District 15, which covers Chesterfield, Hinsdale, Keene Wards 1,3, 4, 5, Surry, Walpole, and Westmoreland, Paul Berch was ousted by Amanda Elizabeth Toll and Renee Monteil, who campaigned together. Most of the races in other House districts were uncontested, with the exception of Districts 4, 9, 11, and 13. In District 4, which represents Keene’s ward 4, Republican Thomas Savastano defeated Matthew Roach. Savastano will face Democrat Jodi Newell who ran unopposed. In District 9, representing Alstead, Gilsum, Marlow, and Stoddard, Republican Rich Nalevanko won his party’s nomination, defeating Robert D’Arcy. Nalevanko will face 16-term incumbent democrat Daniel Adams Easton in November. In District 11, which covers Winchester, Republican Zachary Nutting beat Max Santonastaso. Nutting is up against Democrat Natalie Quevedo. Finally in District 13, the Republican race to represent Dublin and Jaffrey ended with Rita Mattson winning the party’s nomination. Five-term incumbent Richard Ames ran unopposed on the democratic ballot. One thing that will remain the same in Cheshire County is the Mayor of Keene, as George Hansel conceded to New Hampshire District 2 US House of Representatives nominee Bob Burns early this morning. Hansel broke the news on WKBK this morning and said it was a close race. That discussion is available here. Burns now moves ahead to the general ballot where he’ll look to unseat Democrat Annie Kuster. Elsewhere on the ballot, the race for New Hampshire Senate District 10 was a big one as current Senator Jay Kahn was not seeking re-election. For the democrats, Rep. Donovan Fenton came out on top, defeating Keene City Councilor Bobby Williams, and for the Republican’s, Swanzey selectman Sly Karasinksi defeated Ian Freeman. In the statehouse, incumbent republican Governor Chris Sununu won his party’s nomination, and he will be taking on democrat Tom Sherman, who currently serve’s in the State Senate. Sherman discussed his campaign on WKBK Wednesday morning. That discussion is available here. On the national level, incumbent Maggie Hassan won the democratic party nomination for US Senate. Retired Brigadier General Don Bolduc has won the republican nomination. Voters will head to the polls for the general election on November 8th. 4 hours ago in National Marian Shields Robinson, the mother of Michelle Obama who moved with the first family to the White House when son-in-law Barack Obama was elected president, has died. She was 86. 11 hours ago in Local KEENE, N.H. – The head coach of Keene State College softball is resigning to take a position as Parks and… 14 hours ago in National Vermont has become the first state to enact a law requiring fossil fuel companies to pay a share of the damage caused by climate change after the state suffered catastrophic summer flooding and damage from other extreme weather. 1 day ago in Lifestyle, Trending If you use Facebook, WhatsApp or Instagram, you've probably noticed a new character pop up answering search queries or eagerly offering tidbits of information in your feeds, with varying degrees of accuracy. 1 day ago in National, Trending Donald Trump became the first former president to be convicted of felony crimes Thursday as a New York jury found him guilty of falsifying business records in a scheme to illegally influence the 2016 election through hush money payments to a porn actor who said the two had sex.
